# CrewAI Process Documentation Agent

A multi-agent AI crew that analyzes a business process and generates a complete, professional SOP (Standard Operating Procedure) — with measurable thresholds, role ownership, and exception handling.

Built with **CrewAI** + **Google Gemini** (free tier). Runs locally with Python.

## What it does

Give it a business process in plain English (e.g., "student admission process at a private school") and the crew produces:

- A numbered step-by-step process breakdown (inputs, actions, outputs, decision points)
- A full SOP document with purpose, scope, measurable thresholds, per-step ownership, and an exceptions section
- Output saved as `generated_sop.md`

## Architecture

Two agents working in sequence, with task context passing:

```
Input (process description)
        │
        ▼
┌─────────────────────────┐
│  Agent 1: Process       │   Breaks the process into steps —
│  Analyst                │   input / action / output / decisions
└─────────────────────────┘
        │  (task context passed forward)
        ▼
┌─────────────────────────┐
│  Agent 2: SOP Writer    │   Converts the breakdown into a
│                         │   professional SOP with thresholds
└─────────────────────────┘
        │
        ▼
Output: generated_sop.md
```

This implements the **prompt chaining** pattern from Anthropic's "Building Effective Agents" guide — each LLM call has a single responsibility, and output flows sequentially to the next step.

## Tech stack

- Python 3.10+
- [CrewAI](https://github.com/crewAIInc/crewAI) — agent orchestration
- Google Gemini (`gemini-3-flash-preview`) via Google AI Studio free API key

## Setup & run

```bash
# 1. Create and activate a virtual environment
python -m venv crewai-env
crewai-env\Scripts\activate        # Windows
# source crewai-env/bin/activate   # Mac/Linux

# 2. Install dependencies
pip install "crewai[google-genai]"

# 3. Set your Gemini API key (get one free at aistudio.google.com/apikey)
set GEMINI_API_KEY=your_key_here       # Windows
# export GEMINI_API_KEY=your_key_here  # Mac/Linux

# 4. Run
python first_crew.py
```

To document a different process, edit the `inputs={"process": ...}` value at the bottom of `first_crew.py`.

## Sample output

See [`generated_sop.md`](generated_sop.md) for a full SOP generated from a student admission process, including:

- Conditional offers with a 30-day receipt window
- Borderline test score handling (65–69% → re-test or probationary admission)
- Late payment exception (one-time 3-day extension on written request)
- Record retention rules (5-year minimum in SIS)

## Debugging notes (real issues I resolved)

- **`ImportError: Google Gen AI native provider not available`** — CrewAI's Gemini provider ships separately; fixed with `pip install "crewai[google-genai]"`
- **`404 NOT_FOUND: models/gemini-2.5-flash is no longer available`** — model deprecation; updated the model string to `gemini/gemini-3-flash-preview`

## Background

I have hands-on experience building AI agents and automations on visual platforms (n8n, Make, Zapier). This project implements the same orchestration patterns in code: agents map to roles instead of nodes, and `context=[task]` replaces node-to-node data passing. Part of my transition into AI Workflow Analyst roles — combining 8 years of process/education experience with agentic AI tooling.

